SIMPLE: desalinate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: desalinate
<hw>desalinate</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>to remove the salt from,
especially from water; <as>as, it is necessary to <ex>desalinate</ex>
sea water to make it fit to drink</as>.</def> <note>several processes
are in comon use for desalinating sea water. Distillation is effective,
but expensive. <er>Reverse osmosis</er> is more economical.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> desalt, desalinize.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>desalination</ent>⟦br⟧
